1
00:00:40,367 --> 00:00:41,533
Noah.

2
00:00:41,667 --> 00:00:42,633
Just call me Noah.

3
00:00:42,767 --> 00:00:45,333
So Noah's a good guy after all.

4
00:00:45,467 --> 00:00:49,667
I didn't expect he'd help us.

5
00:00:49,800 --> 00:00:53,133
Manuel sent some money.

6
00:00:53,267 --> 00:00:54,467
He knew?

7
00:00:54,600 --> 00:00:56,367
They called, sis.

8
00:00:56,500 --> 00:00:58,767
Your ex wanted to talk to you
so badly.

9
00:00:58,900 --> 00:01:00,867
Let's put an end to this.

10
00:01:01,000 --> 00:01:02,400
Hold on.

11
00:01:02,533 --> 00:01:03,967
What about the kids?

12
00:01:04,100 --> 00:01:06,700
We'll survive even without you.

13
00:01:06,833 --> 00:01:09,800
Thank you so much for all
the years.

14
00:01:22,233 --> 00:01:23,667
- Hi, Dad.
- Hey.

15
00:01:23,800 --> 00:01:25,567
You came right on time.

16
00:01:25,700 --> 00:01:27,867
I'm done cooking dinner.

17
00:01:28,000 --> 00:01:30,933
Wow!

18
00:01:32,400 --> 00:01:33,667
Dad.

19
00:01:34,900 --> 00:01:36,633
Come on.

20
00:01:36,767 --> 00:01:39,867
Oh, my God! You cooked
my favorite!

21
00:01:40,000 --> 00:01:42,200
Of course, you'll want
to eat more

22
00:01:42,367 --> 00:01:44,967
and focus better on your
studies. Right?

23
00:01:45,100 --> 00:01:46,167
I'm excited.

24
00:01:46,300 --> 00:01:48,567
I have something, too. It came
from the Philippines.

25
00:01:48,700 --> 00:01:50,033
You can cook it, Manuel.

26
00:01:50,167 --> 00:01:51,067
This is good, too.

27
00:01:51,200 --> 00:01:52,633
Okay, okay. Go and change
your clothes.

28
00:01:52,767 --> 00:01:54,700
And put your dirty clothes
in the laundry

29
00:01:54,833 --> 00:01:56,767
so I can wash them tomorrow.

30
00:01:56,900 --> 00:01:59,167
Go on, before the food
gets cold.

31
00:02:17,000 --> 00:02:19,000
<i> Love, here's your favorite.</i>

32
00:02:19,633 --> 00:02:20,900
<i>It seems that it will take
a long while</i>

33
00:02:21,033 --> 00:02:22,433
<i>before I can cook for you again.</i>

34
00:02:23,033 --> 00:02:24,400
<i>Come on, I haven't even
left yet,</i>

35
00:02:24,533 --> 00:02:26,900
<i>and you're already making me
miss you!</i>

36
00:02:36,300 --> 00:02:38,233
Thank you so much, everyone.

37
00:02:39,067 --> 00:02:42,367
It means a lot to me
to see you here

38
00:02:43,200 --> 00:02:45,967
and celebrate with me
as I've fulfilled my dreams.

39
00:02:46,500 --> 00:02:48,267
I want to thank many people.

40
00:02:48,433 --> 00:02:52,933
First of all, to my best friend,
Paz.

41
00:02:53,067 --> 00:02:55,133
Because you're the one who's
most persistent

42
00:02:55,267 --> 00:02:56,667
in looking for customers.

43
00:02:56,800 --> 00:02:59,067
It seems that you convinced
all your relatives

44
00:02:59,200 --> 00:03:01,767
and friends to buy my products.

45
00:03:02,233 --> 00:03:03,467
Thank you.

46
00:03:04,367 --> 00:03:07,667
This business wouldn't have
grown if not for the trust

47
00:03:08,333 --> 00:03:10,133
of a good friend.

48
00:03:11,833 --> 00:03:14,033
Because of the capital
he has lent me,

49
00:03:14,167 --> 00:03:16,167
the business has started
to grow.

50
00:03:17,900 --> 00:03:19,667
Thank you so much, Noah.

51
00:03:21,767 --> 00:03:26,567
If it wasn't for you,
I wouldn't be here now.

52
00:03:29,467 --> 00:03:33,567
I also thank the most important
people in my life.

53
00:03:34,200 --> 00:03:35,333
My children.

54
00:03:36,867 --> 00:03:40,233
Jeffrey, Andrea, Coleen...

55
00:03:40,967 --> 00:03:43,267
since the beginning, you've been
my life partners.

56
00:03:44,133 --> 00:03:47,500
You give me strength
and inspiration,

57
00:03:48,000 --> 00:03:51,500
especially when
I feel discouraged.

58
00:03:53,033 --> 00:03:54,933
I love you all so much.

59
00:03:55,100 --> 00:03:56,200
I love you, Mom.

60
00:03:56,333 --> 00:03:59,100
I love you, Mom!

61
00:04:00,300 --> 00:04:02,767
Thank you so much, everyone.

62
00:04:02,900 --> 00:04:05,800
Thank you to our hardworking
staff.

63
00:04:06,700 --> 00:04:09,333
You're part of this success.

64
00:04:09,467 --> 00:04:12,467
And most of all, to our God.

65
00:04:12,600 --> 00:04:16,167
Because this blessing came
from Him.

66
00:04:17,333 --> 00:04:23,933
I want us to celebrate today.
So, let's eat together.

67
00:04:24,067 --> 00:04:26,800
Congratulations!

68
00:04:26,933 --> 00:04:28,433
- Yes!
- Thank you.

69
00:04:31,567 --> 00:04:34,367
- Thank you!
- I'm so envious, Mom!

70
00:04:34,500 --> 00:04:37,400
- Come on, let's eat.
- Congrats, Mom!

71
00:04:37,533 --> 00:04:38,867
Mom, look at Jeff!

72
00:04:39,733 --> 00:04:43,433
Come on, look! We have prepared
lots of food.

73
00:04:47,767 --> 00:04:49,000
- Dad.
- Do you want more?

74
00:04:50,400 --> 00:04:53,500
Dad, I'm a big girl now. You
don't have to do that anymore.

75
00:04:53,633 --> 00:04:54,667
Come on.

76
00:04:54,800 --> 00:04:59,000
Even if your hair becomes white,
you'll remain my baby.

77
00:04:59,533 --> 00:05:02,867
- How sweet!
- Of course!

78
00:05:09,133 --> 00:05:15,100
Dad, how about Mommy?

79
00:05:15,700 --> 00:05:16,867
- One more?
- No, that's enough.

80
00:05:17,433 --> 00:05:19,033
I don't like longanisa
that much.

81
00:05:19,967 --> 00:05:23,533
Mom, your friend is right.
The longanisa is good.

82
00:05:23,667 --> 00:05:24,933
Right, Dad?

83
00:05:25,067 --> 00:05:25,667
Yes.

84
00:05:26,367 --> 00:05:28,067
Do you know what I miss?

85
00:05:28,700 --> 00:05:30,533
The kebab in Saudi Arabia.

86
00:05:31,900 --> 00:05:33,300
You miss Saudi Arabia?

87
00:05:35,133 --> 00:05:35,867
Yeah.

88
00:05:36,467 --> 00:05:38,067
But I love my life here.

89
00:05:39,133 --> 00:05:41,633
I'm still thankful for all
the opportunities

90
00:05:41,767 --> 00:05:43,867
that opened up for me here
in Canada.

91
00:05:44,000 --> 00:05:47,167
And because of my work, we enjoy
the benefits of living here.

92
00:05:47,800 --> 00:05:49,433
Yeah, like my allowance.

93
00:05:50,733 --> 00:05:53,100
And Dad doesn't have to work.

94
00:05:53,233 --> 00:05:55,633
Which means more time for me.

95
00:05:56,933 --> 00:05:58,833
How about you, Dad? Do you miss
Saudi Arabia?

96
00:06:00,733 --> 00:06:02,300
I didn't stay there that long.

97
00:06:03,233 --> 00:06:06,267
And I'm happy here
because we're together.

98
00:06:07,933 --> 00:06:09,333
I'm with you and your mom.

99
00:06:10,800 --> 00:06:12,367
Are you happy here?

100
00:06:12,500 --> 00:06:13,500
Of course!

101
00:06:13,633 --> 00:06:15,000
You and Mom are here.

102
00:06:15,133 --> 00:06:16,233
My friends are here.

103
00:06:16,367 --> 00:06:18,267
That's what matters. Right, Dad?

104
00:06:18,400 --> 00:06:20,967
We're with our loved ones.

105
00:06:22,067 --> 00:06:23,100
Of course.

106
00:06:29,533 --> 00:06:31,167
Your Aunt Hilda's calling.
Excuse me.

107
00:06:34,433 --> 00:06:35,033
Hello.

108
00:06:35,800 --> 00:06:37,167
How is everything there?

109
00:06:37,933 --> 00:06:38,633
What?

110
00:07:00,600 --> 00:07:03,867
I've been away from my mother
for so long because of work.

111
00:07:04,567 --> 00:07:07,433
I keep complaining about
their expenses.

112
00:07:09,433 --> 00:07:10,500
The truth is,

113
00:07:11,333 --> 00:07:13,167
I love them so much,
especially my mom.

114
00:07:13,900 --> 00:07:18,100
That's why I want to see
her even for the last time.

115
00:07:20,533 --> 00:07:23,600
Mom, can Daddy and I go
with you?

116
00:07:24,300 --> 00:07:25,867
I want to see Grandma, too.

117
00:07:26,000 --> 00:07:28,867
I only see her on video calls.

118
00:07:30,067 --> 00:07:30,933
Dear,

119
00:07:31,900 --> 00:07:33,833
what about your school?

120
00:07:33,967 --> 00:07:36,433
I can miss my classes.

121
00:07:36,567 --> 00:07:40,200
I also want to meet Aunt Hilda
and the rest of the relatives.

122
00:07:40,667 --> 00:07:42,233
And also on Dad's side.

123
00:07:43,233 --> 00:07:44,767
Mom, please?

124
00:07:45,333 --> 00:07:46,367
Are you sure?

125
00:07:48,833 --> 00:07:49,733
Okay.

126
00:07:50,233 --> 00:07:50,900
Thanks, Mom.

127
00:07:51,033 --> 00:07:51,833
- I love you!
- I love you.

128
00:07:51,967 --> 00:07:53,533
- I'll pack my stuff now.
- Sure.

129
00:07:53,667 --> 00:07:54,667
You, too, Dad.

130
00:08:00,733 --> 00:08:01,633
Manuel,

131
00:08:03,033 --> 00:08:04,933
I just want to make it clear to
you.

132
00:08:05,667 --> 00:08:07,600
We're only going home
to the Philippines

133
00:08:07,733 --> 00:08:09,300
for my mom's funeral.

134
00:08:09,567 --> 00:08:11,200
And nothing else.

135
00:08:13,200 --> 00:08:15,033
Hazel, it's been a long time.

136
00:08:17,033 --> 00:08:18,967
I'm too ashamed to face them.

137
00:08:21,200 --> 00:08:21,933
Good.

138
00:08:23,233 --> 00:08:24,633
Let's go and pack our bags.

139
00:08:52,900 --> 00:08:53,967
I'm so happy, sis.

140
00:08:54,100 --> 00:08:58,267
I remember, you used to sell
longanisa in our house.

141
00:08:58,433 --> 00:09:00,533
And now you already have your
store. I'm so happy.

142
00:09:00,667 --> 00:09:01,733
Yes, super true.

143
00:09:01,867 --> 00:09:04,067
My Godmother's hard work
and perseverance

144
00:09:04,200 --> 00:09:05,400
have already paid off.

145
00:09:06,333 --> 00:09:11,433
It's more like God blesses
those who have been wronged.

146
00:09:11,567 --> 00:09:13,633
It was actually a blessing
in disguise

147
00:09:13,767 --> 00:09:15,467
that your godfather left her.

148
00:09:15,600 --> 00:09:18,900
Look at her. She can already
stand up on her...

149
00:09:24,700 --> 00:09:25,867
Sorry.

150
00:09:26,533 --> 00:09:28,100
Auntie, we shouldn't be
talking about someone

151
00:09:28,267 --> 00:09:29,267
who isn't here anymore.

152
00:09:30,500 --> 00:09:31,933
And it's been a long time since,
Auntie.

153
00:09:32,467 --> 00:09:34,300
We have already moved on.

154
00:09:35,167 --> 00:09:38,900
Andeng, Jeff, and Felma,
I'm sorry.

155
00:09:39,033 --> 00:09:43,867
Your Godmother is so tactless.

156
00:09:45,267 --> 00:09:47,800
I'm sorry, too, Noah. I didn't
mean to say that.

157
00:09:47,933 --> 00:09:50,100
You've taken on the role
of father to the kids

158
00:09:50,233 --> 00:09:51,500
for such a long time.

159
00:09:51,633 --> 00:09:55,000
You know what? I'm thirsty.
Excuse me.

160
00:10:05,267 --> 00:10:06,000
Hey, hey.

161
00:10:06,133 --> 00:10:07,433
You've been eating
since earlier.

162
00:10:07,567 --> 00:10:09,233
You keep trying our products,
but you're not buying them.

163
00:10:10,467 --> 00:10:12,233
I'm just trying a little
of everything.

164
00:10:12,367 --> 00:10:13,700
You've eaten a lot.

165
00:10:13,833 --> 00:10:16,367
You've almost finished
all the free samples.

166
00:10:16,500 --> 00:10:17,533
It's on display.

167
00:10:17,667 --> 00:10:19,700
- So we have to try it.
- I've given you enough already.

168
00:10:19,833 --> 00:10:20,567
Rose,

169
00:10:21,567 --> 00:10:22,533
is there a problem?

170
00:10:22,667 --> 00:10:26,567
Sir, this kid has been
eating for a while now.

171
00:10:26,700 --> 00:10:28,600
She's almost finished
the free samples.

172
00:10:28,733 --> 00:10:30,333
Where are your parents?

173
00:10:30,633 --> 00:10:31,567
They're not here.

174
00:10:32,767 --> 00:10:35,867
You'd better call them. And tell
them to buy.

175
00:10:36,333 --> 00:10:37,200
Okay.

176
00:10:46,967 --> 00:10:48,033
I know you.

177
00:10:49,233 --> 00:10:49,767
What?

178
00:10:57,267 --> 00:10:57,900
What did you say?

179
00:10:59,067 --> 00:11:00,333
This is you, right?

180
00:11:03,800 --> 00:11:04,800
Where did you get that?

181
00:11:05,300 --> 00:11:06,433
Wait a minute.

182
00:11:07,100 --> 00:11:08,767
Confirm first that it's you.

183
00:11:10,200 --> 00:11:10,933
Yes, it's me.

184
00:11:12,600 --> 00:11:14,200
It's me. Where did you get this?

185
00:11:16,767 --> 00:11:18,000
Dad?

186
00:11:19,900 --> 00:11:21,000
Dad!

187
00:11:27,000 --> 00:11:28,367
Dad.

188
00:11:35,000 --> 00:11:36,400
Wait. Come here.

189
00:11:37,100 --> 00:11:39,300
What do you mean by dad? I don't
know you. Who are you?

190
00:11:40,567 --> 00:11:43,133
I'm Cristina.

191
00:11:43,767 --> 00:11:45,833
- Tetay for short.
- I don't know you.

192
00:11:46,267 --> 00:11:48,133
I know you.

193
00:11:48,700 --> 00:11:51,767
You're Jeffrey Cruz, right?

194
00:11:52,600 --> 00:11:53,667
How did you know that?

195
00:11:54,100 --> 00:11:55,467
My mom told me.

196
00:11:55,600 --> 00:11:58,867
- She told me you are my dad.
-Tetay!

197
00:12:08,000 --> 00:12:08,900
Daisy?

198
00:12:10,033 --> 00:12:12,400
Dad's here, Mom.

199
00:12:13,300 --> 00:12:14,267
- What's that?
- Let's go!

200
00:12:14,400 --> 00:12:16,167
- Mom! It's Dad!
- I said let's go!

201
00:12:16,333 --> 00:12:18,833
- We're going home!
- Dad!

202
00:12:18,967 --> 00:12:19,833
- Dad!
- You're so stubborn!

203
00:12:20,533 --> 00:12:23,933
Dad! Dad! Dad!

204
00:12:26,333 --> 00:12:27,133
Dad!

205
00:12:29,100 --> 00:12:30,600
What's that?

206
00:12:33,800 --> 00:12:35,167
Jeff, who was that?

207
00:12:35,300 --> 00:12:37,433
Jeff, why did she call you Dad?

208
00:12:38,933 --> 00:12:40,100
You have a kid?

209
00:12:49,733 --> 00:12:51,733
Come on, Mom!

210
00:12:51,867 --> 00:12:52,333
Let's go.

211
00:12:52,467 --> 00:12:55,967
Dad's there!

212
00:12:56,100 --> 00:12:59,600
Why are we leaving? I don't want
to go, Mom!

213
00:13:00,233 --> 00:13:03,300
You told me that he went abroad.

214
00:13:03,433 --> 00:13:05,300
But he's here!

215
00:13:07,900 --> 00:13:09,700
Are you mad at him?

216
00:13:11,633 --> 00:13:14,633
I'm not mad at him.

217
00:13:15,533 --> 00:13:16,500
But....

218
00:13:17,367 --> 00:13:19,300
why did Dad say that?

219
00:13:20,500 --> 00:13:22,367
He said he didn't have a child.

220
00:13:23,000 --> 00:13:25,367
So, what am I?

221
00:13:25,967 --> 00:13:30,433
I'm his daughter, right?

222
00:13:30,567 --> 00:13:31,900
Please, Tetay!

223
00:13:32,033 --> 00:13:33,367
Stop asking questions.

224
00:13:33,500 --> 00:13:38,033
Please answer it. So that
I won't ask you anymore.

225
00:13:38,167 --> 00:13:39,833
Don't be stubborn.

226
00:13:39,967 --> 00:13:43,133
And next time, never leave
my side again!

227
00:13:43,267 --> 00:13:45,167
We'll get in trouble because of
your stubbornness!

228
00:13:45,300 --> 00:13:47,500
What do you mean by we'll get
in trouble?

229
00:13:47,633 --> 00:13:48,867
How come?

230
00:13:49,600 --> 00:13:50,833
I said stop!

231
00:13:50,967 --> 00:13:55,200
Mom! It's Dad!

232
00:13:55,367 --> 00:13:57,333
Jeffrey, come here.

233
00:13:59,567 --> 00:14:01,167
Tell me the truth.

234
00:14:02,933 --> 00:14:03,967
Did you have a child?

235
00:14:06,700 --> 00:14:08,367
Is that kid your daughter?

236
00:14:09,733 --> 00:14:11,900
- I don't know, Mom.
- You don't know?

237
00:14:12,800 --> 00:14:13,800
She was your girlfriend,

238
00:14:13,933 --> 00:14:14,800
something happened between
the two of you.

239
00:14:14,933 --> 00:14:15,767
You got her pregnant. And you
didn't know?

240
00:14:16,167 --> 00:14:18,000
Jeff, you didn't tell us
you had a girlfriend!

241
00:14:18,133 --> 00:14:20,167
Do I have to tell
you everything?

242
00:14:20,300 --> 00:14:21,300
You should!

243
00:14:21,433 --> 00:14:22,800
We're family!

244
00:14:22,933 --> 00:14:24,600
We shouldn't be hiding
anything from each other.

245
00:14:24,733 --> 00:14:26,433
It wasn't serious, Mom.

246
00:14:26,567 --> 00:14:28,000
Wasn't serious?

247
00:14:28,167 --> 00:14:29,733
But you got her pregnant.

248
00:14:29,867 --> 00:14:31,267
Who is that woman?

249
00:14:32,100 --> 00:14:35,167
Her name's Daisy. She's a market
vendor. We became together.

250
00:14:35,300 --> 00:14:37,833
One day, she told me she was
pregnant and I was the father.

251
00:14:37,967 --> 00:14:39,633
What did you do?

252
00:14:39,767 --> 00:14:40,900
Nothing.

253
00:14:41,033 --> 00:14:43,267
Mom, I don't believe her.

254
00:14:43,400 --> 00:14:45,667
We stopped talking. I stopped
seeing her.

255
00:14:46,133 --> 00:14:47,600
Jeff, you ghosted him?

256
00:14:50,833 --> 00:14:53,600
Jeffrey, what year did
it happen?

257
00:14:54,300 --> 00:14:55,767
I think I was 20 years
old at that time.

258
00:14:57,067 --> 00:14:58,600
It's been almost 9 years.

259
00:15:00,067 --> 00:15:01,500
And that kid...

260
00:15:02,267 --> 00:15:04,533
With her height and looks,

261
00:15:04,867 --> 00:15:06,533
she seems to be nine years old
already!

262
00:15:10,800 --> 00:15:12,367
She could be your daughter!

263
00:15:12,967 --> 00:15:14,533
That's definitely his daughter.

264
00:15:14,667 --> 00:15:16,200
But what did he do?

265
00:15:16,333 --> 00:15:17,767
He abandoned the kid's mom.

266
00:15:17,900 --> 00:15:19,533
He ran away when he got
her pregnant.

267
00:15:19,667 --> 00:15:21,367
He abandoned the kid.

268
00:15:21,500 --> 00:15:22,700
What do we call you, Jeff?

269
00:15:22,833 --> 00:15:23,867
You have the nerve!

270
00:15:24,000 --> 00:15:25,800
What's your problem? I wasn't
ready at that time.

271
00:15:25,933 --> 00:15:26,767
If you weren't ready,

272
00:15:26,900 --> 00:15:28,333
you shouldn't have gotten
her pregnant!

273
00:15:28,467 --> 00:15:30,000
Poor kid!

274
00:15:30,133 --> 00:15:31,467
Why are you getting mad?

275
00:15:31,600 --> 00:15:32,533
Jeffrey.

276
00:15:32,667 --> 00:15:34,367
Why wouldn't I get mad?

277
00:15:34,500 --> 00:15:36,067
We'd been through
the same thing.

278
00:15:36,233 --> 00:15:38,700
You know what it feels
like to be left behind.

279
00:15:39,067 --> 00:15:41,033
Your dad left us, too!

280
00:15:41,167 --> 00:15:44,300
You know how it feels to get
abandoned, but you did it, too.

281
00:15:44,433 --> 00:15:46,667
What makes you different
from that man?

282
00:15:46,800 --> 00:15:47,600
You're the same as him!

283
00:15:47,733 --> 00:15:49,233
Don't compare me with that man!

284
00:15:49,367 --> 00:15:50,600
- Stop it!
- I'm not like him!

285
00:15:50,733 --> 00:15:51,867
That's enough!

286
00:15:52,567 --> 00:15:54,133
Stop bringing up the past!

287
00:15:54,267 --> 00:15:56,333
That ended a long time ago.

288
00:15:56,467 --> 00:15:58,133
Talk to your daughter.

289
00:15:58,267 --> 00:15:59,300
She's acting like a mom again.

290
00:15:59,433 --> 00:16:01,567
Hey! You're not my mother!

291
00:16:01,700 --> 00:16:02,600
Jeff...

292
00:16:34,933 --> 00:16:36,100
Hello?

293
00:16:39,400 --> 00:16:40,000
Hello?

294
00:16:42,133 --> 00:16:43,900
Yes, I'm already here.

295
00:16:45,133 --> 00:16:46,667
They're with me.

296
00:16:49,400 --> 00:16:51,067
That's you, Dad.

297
00:16:51,200 --> 00:16:52,133
This is me.

298
00:16:52,267 --> 00:16:53,433
This is Mom.

299
00:16:53,567 --> 00:16:55,833
She's carrying Coleen.

300
00:16:55,967 --> 00:16:57,500
And Jeffrey.

301
00:16:57,633 --> 00:17:01,367
Look at it whenever
you miss us.

302
00:17:01,800 --> 00:17:02,533
Thank you, dear.

303
00:17:02,667 --> 00:17:04,433
Be safe always.

304
00:17:04,567 --> 00:17:06,133
Love, take care.

305
00:17:10,400 --> 00:17:12,500
Dad, are you okay?

306
00:17:22,500 --> 00:17:23,467
Yes, I'm okay.

307
00:17:25,033 --> 00:17:26,667
I just missed the Philippines.

308
00:17:29,800 --> 00:17:30,600
Really?

309
00:17:33,067 --> 00:17:34,733
Mom, give it to Dad.

310
00:17:35,200 --> 00:17:38,567
He must really have missed
this place. It's been years.

311
00:17:41,867 --> 00:17:43,433
Is the one picking us not
here yet?

312
00:17:46,000 --> 00:17:49,167
- There it is, Dad. Let's go?
- Finally.

313
00:17:55,300 --> 00:17:57,533
Mister, please help me
with this.

314
00:17:58,833 --> 00:18:00,033
Get inside the car.

315
00:18:00,600 --> 00:18:01,467
I'll take care of these.

316
00:18:33,900 --> 00:18:36,967
Please put the sticker properly.

317
00:18:37,100 --> 00:18:39,633
So that it can pass
the quality control.

318
00:18:39,767 --> 00:18:40,800
Yes, Ma'am.

319
00:18:44,133 --> 00:18:46,400
Good afternoon, Ma'am.

320
00:18:47,433 --> 00:18:48,100
Andrea!

321
00:18:48,567 --> 00:18:49,267
Yes?

322
00:18:49,567 --> 00:18:50,700
Have you and Jeff
already reconciled?

323
00:18:54,700 --> 00:18:57,300
Aren't you curious if that kid
really is Jeff's daughter?

324
00:18:58,000 --> 00:19:00,567
If that's his kid, that means
we're already aunties!

325
00:19:00,700 --> 00:19:02,633
Andrea, we already have a niece!

326
00:19:02,767 --> 00:19:03,767
Be quiet.

327
00:19:06,367 --> 00:19:09,067
We can't acknowledge
the kid that quick.

328
00:19:09,200 --> 00:19:11,833
Of course, her father
should do it first.

329
00:19:12,533 --> 00:19:13,867
What is Jeff's plan?

330
00:19:15,800 --> 00:19:16,567
I don't know.

331
00:19:17,867 --> 00:19:22,867
It's up to him if he decides
to abandon the kid.

332
00:19:24,067 --> 00:19:25,933
Do you really have to talk about
me here?

333
00:19:27,833 --> 00:19:29,567
Go home, Coleen.
Look at the time.

334
00:19:29,733 --> 00:19:31,767
The people are working here.
Stop bothering them.

335
00:19:32,767 --> 00:19:34,900
- Okay. Thank you so much.
- Andrea.

336
00:19:37,300 --> 00:19:40,500
He's in a bad temper
because he's burdened...

337
00:19:41,233 --> 00:19:42,367
Mom.

338
00:19:42,500 --> 00:19:46,133
Coleen, can you tell your
brother I want to talk to him?

339
00:19:47,000 --> 00:19:47,800
Okay, Mom.

340
00:19:56,100 --> 00:19:58,767
Keep moving. So we can
finish early.

341
00:20:05,733 --> 00:20:10,233
I hate it when you
and your siblings fight.

342
00:20:11,033 --> 00:20:13,300
Andrea was way
out of line, Mom.

343
00:20:14,267 --> 00:20:15,800
She has a point.

344
00:20:16,767 --> 00:20:20,233
Why did you abandon your kid
and her mother?

345
00:20:24,600 --> 00:20:25,933
I got nervous, Mom.

346
00:20:28,267 --> 00:20:30,133
I was too young. What do I know
about being a father?

347
00:20:31,733 --> 00:20:34,667
I didn't finish my studies.

348
00:20:35,167 --> 00:20:36,567
I was jobless.

349
00:20:38,567 --> 00:20:41,900
And our business wasn't doing
that well yet.

350
00:20:42,867 --> 00:20:44,600
So, how would I raise the kid?

351
00:20:49,567 --> 00:20:51,800
Why didn't you ask me for help?

352
00:20:53,533 --> 00:20:55,200
You had a lot on your mind
already, Mom.

353
00:20:56,467 --> 00:20:58,867
I didn't want to add
to your burden.

354
00:21:00,900 --> 00:21:01,667
Jeff...

355
00:21:02,700 --> 00:21:03,333
Jeffrey...

356
00:21:04,067 --> 00:21:05,200
I'm your mother.

357
00:21:06,233 --> 00:21:07,867
We're family.

358
00:21:10,067 --> 00:21:14,200
We promised that we'd help each
other, right?

359
00:21:16,967 --> 00:21:17,833
Right?

360
00:21:21,367 --> 00:21:22,867
What's your plan now?

361
00:21:33,167 --> 00:21:38,833
If she's really your daughter,
do not abandon her.

362
00:21:40,067 --> 00:21:41,467
She needs a father.

363
00:21:42,500 --> 00:21:47,433
And Daisy needs someone to help
her raise the kid.

364
00:21:49,733 --> 00:21:52,300
We'd been through that,
didn't we?

365
00:21:52,600 --> 00:21:57,200
You know how painful
it is to be alone.

366
00:21:57,967 --> 00:21:58,633
Mom.

367
00:22:00,500 --> 00:22:02,533
Mom, I thought we wouldn't
bring up the past?

368
00:22:03,667 --> 00:22:09,167
My only point is, don't
let your kid and her mother

369
00:22:09,567 --> 00:22:11,400
go through the same thing that
we had experienced.

370
00:22:44,233 --> 00:22:45,067
Felma,

371
00:22:46,800 --> 00:22:47,533
are you okay?

372
00:22:52,233 --> 00:22:58,333
I just remember those times
when I was raising my kids.

373
00:23:00,100 --> 00:23:01,333
Do you remember Manuel?

374
00:23:02,600 --> 00:23:05,400
I remember the struggle more
than I remember him.

375
00:23:06,233 --> 00:23:08,267
And that's what my kids
also remember.

376
00:23:11,333 --> 00:23:13,033
If Daisy didn't come,

377
00:23:13,933 --> 00:23:19,600
I wouldn't find out that Jeffrey
and Andrea haven't moved on yet.

378
00:23:20,600 --> 00:23:21,533
Even now,

379
00:23:22,633 --> 00:23:25,867
they're still in pain by what
their father did to them.

380
00:23:27,200 --> 00:23:28,233
How about you, Felma?

381
00:23:30,400 --> 00:23:31,900
Are you still hurting?

382
00:23:34,033 --> 00:23:36,033
It hurts me more to see
my children in pain.

383
00:23:38,200 --> 00:23:40,700
I feel that I have shortcomings.

384
00:23:45,533 --> 00:23:47,833
I promised them to be
their mother and father.

385
00:23:47,967 --> 00:23:49,800
But what have I done for them?

386
00:23:55,833 --> 00:23:58,700
Maybe that's why Jeffrey
made the wrong decision.

387
00:23:59,333 --> 00:24:01,500
He abandoned his own kid.

388
00:24:02,267 --> 00:24:05,300
It would've been different
if he had a father to guide him.

389
00:24:11,200 --> 00:24:12,900
You still remember Manuel.

390
00:24:13,333 --> 00:24:14,033
No.

391
00:24:16,500 --> 00:24:17,900
It's been over between
us for a long time.

392
00:24:19,067 --> 00:24:22,367
But we still haven't started.

393
00:24:23,600 --> 00:24:24,733
Noah...

394
00:24:26,600 --> 00:24:27,400
Felma,

395
00:24:29,533 --> 00:24:30,433
all I'm asking...

396
00:24:32,233 --> 00:24:33,700
is a chance for me to love you.

397
00:24:34,300 --> 00:24:35,933
We're friends.

398
00:24:37,133 --> 00:24:39,400
You're a part of our family,
too.

399
00:24:40,067 --> 00:24:41,367
But that's not enough.

400
00:24:42,233 --> 00:24:43,433
Something still seems
to be missing.

401
00:24:44,833 --> 00:24:47,033
Why don't you look
at someone else?

402
00:24:47,867 --> 00:24:50,000
I already feel ashamed.

403
00:24:50,500 --> 00:24:53,433
I don't want you to feel
that I'm just leading you on.

404
00:24:55,467 --> 00:25:00,067
Does it mean I have a chance?

405
00:25:05,033 --> 00:25:05,933
Felma,

406
00:25:07,367 --> 00:25:08,267
I will wait.

407
00:25:09,567 --> 00:25:14,767
And I'll wait some more
until you learn to love me.

408
00:25:23,767 --> 00:25:25,833
I heard you tried to see Daisy,
Jeff.

409
00:25:25,967 --> 00:25:27,067
Why didn't you go through
with it?

410
00:25:27,200 --> 00:25:28,133
He became coward.

411
00:25:28,267 --> 00:25:29,600
I don't know what
to tell them.

412
00:25:29,733 --> 00:25:32,133
Just admit that
you're like your father.

413
00:25:32,267 --> 00:25:33,600
Don't compare me to your father.

414
00:25:33,733 --> 00:25:34,667
Our father.

415
00:25:34,800 --> 00:25:35,733
Stop it.

416
00:25:35,900 --> 00:25:38,467
Can I get Felma's number
and address?

417
00:25:38,600 --> 00:25:40,567
I don't want to get beaten
by Paz.

418
00:25:40,700 --> 00:25:42,333
You want to talk to Felma?

419
00:25:42,467 --> 00:25:43,167
Where's your dad?

420
00:25:43,300 --> 00:25:45,167
He left. He said
he'd go somewhere.

421
00:25:45,300 --> 00:25:45,800
Where?

422
00:25:46,067 --> 00:25:47,467
I didn't ask him, Mom.

423
00:25:47,900 --> 00:25:50,467
Roviel, I'd be at the salon at
1:30 PM.

424
00:25:51,133 --> 00:25:52,200
<i> Sure, Mother.</i>

425
00:25:52,467 --> 00:25:53,400
Okay, thank you.
